I've been here twice and had a great time both nights.
It doesn't get too packed here and the crowd seems to be a little older than the more popular night clubs.
Drink prices are decent.
One night we went, there was a magician over by one of the bars performing magic.
I was absolutely mind blown.
The view overlooking the body of water and the fountains is spectacular and it's also great when you need some fresh after dancing for a while.
Hyde might not have the appeal of an XS, Marquee, or Hakkasan, and it certainly isn't for everyone, but it's been perfect for me the times that I've gone.

