It was extra special walking into the club and seeing the gorgeous and dramatic up-close view of the Bellagio fountain show going on in the backdrop.
If you stand right at the balcony during the fountain show, you might get misted on!
But it was fun!
We were on the free guest list and arrived early, around 10:40pm on a Saturday night.
The line wasn't too long at all, probably a 10 minute wait at most.
As the evening progressed, the place got packed!
It's very tight quarters inside with a tiny dance floor and not much space to dance.
Definitely arrive early in order to enjoy the venue.
The music was your typical club hip hop.
Nothing out of the ordinary and nothing that really got me in the mood to dance.
The bouncers here were a step above in the professional department, unlike Hakkasan.
